    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Mets pitcher Al Leiter was presented before the game as the recipient of the 2000 Roberto Clemente Award, given to the major league player who combines skills on the field with a sense of civic responsibility.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Mets pitcher Al Leiter was presented before the game as the recipient of the 2000 Roberto Clemente Award, given to the major league player who combines skills on the field with a sense of civic responsibility.</p>
        <p>Leiter and his wife, Lori, established Leiters Landing two years ago. The foundation helps children in need through a variety of programs based in education, health care and social and community service. The award honors Roberto Clemente, who died in a plane crash while delivering supplies to earthquake-stricken Nicaragua.</p>
        <p>Steve Popper</p>
        <p>BASEBALL: SUBWAY SERIES -- NOTEBOOK</p>
      </block>
